HealthEData_1Sandbox

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

http://www.fhir.org/guides/healthedata1-sandbox/ImplementationGuide/healthedata1-sandbox

This is a Healthedata1 sandbox for creation of resources and examples

name: HealthEData_1Sandbox
title: Health eData 1 Sandbox
description: This is a Healthedata1 sandbox for creation of resources and examples

resource.name: Questionnaire URL Extension
resource.description: The location where a non-FHIR questionnaire/survey form can be found. This extension is used when the survey,form, or questionnaire which is being anwered is not a FHIR [Questionnaire](https://www.hl7.org/fhir/questionnaire.html), otherwise the [canonical url](https://www.hl7.org/fhir/references.html#canonical) for the FHIR Questionnaire is used.

resource.name: US Core Encounter Diagnosis Profile
resource.description: The US Core Encounter Diagnosis Profile is based upon the core FHIR Condition Resource and meets the  U.S. Core Data for Interoperability (USCDI) v2 'Encounter Diagnosis' requirements.  It defines constraints and extensions on the Condition resource for the minimal set of data to record, search, and fetch information about an encounter diagnosis.fhirVersion: 4.0.1

resource.name: US Core Observation Survey Profile
resource.description: Profile for Observations to record responses from  a survey or questionnaire.  It can be used to represent individual responses, panels of multi-question surveys, and multi-select responses to “check all that apply” questions.

resource.name: US Core Problems and Health Concerns Profile
resource.description: The US Core Problems and Health Concerns Profile is based upon the core FHIR Condition Resource and meets the  U.S. Core Data for Interoperability (USCDI) v2 'Problems' and 'Health Concerns' requirements and SDOH 'Problems/Health Concerns' requirements.  It defines constraints and extensions on the Condition resource for the minimal set of data to record, search, and fetch information about a condition, diagnosis, or other event, situation, issue, or clinical concept that is documented and categorized as a problem or health concern including information about a Social Determinants of Health-related condition.fhirVersion: 4.0.1

resource.name: US Core Questionnaire Response Profile
resource.description: Defines how to represent answers from surveys/questionnaires.  This profile is based on the [SDC Questionnaire Response]

resource.name: US Core Observation SDOH Assessment Profile
resource.description: Profile for Observations to record responses derived from Social Determinants of Health (SDOH) assessment instruments.  It is derived from the US Core Observation Survey Profile and can be used to represent individual responses, panels of multi-question surveys, and multi-select “check all that apply” questions. This profile  meets the U.S. Core Data for Interoperability (USCDI) v2 SDOH Assessments requirements.

resource.name: US Core Imaging Codes
resource.description: This value set includes all LOINC values whose CLASS is "RAD" in the LOINC database (Refer to [Appendix A](https://loinc.org/kb/users-guide/loinc-database-structure/) of LOINC Users' Guide)

resource.name: US Core Survey Codes
resource.description: This value set includes all LOINC values whose CLASSTYPE is SURVEY in the LOINC database (Refer to [Appendix A](https://loinc.org/kb/users-guide/loinc-database-structure/) of LOINC Users' Guide)
